claim.claim-text:
21. A method for making a magnetorheological fluid comprising:
a) forming a supramolecular polymer gel in a first solvent;
b) adding the supramolecular gel and the first solvent to a second solvent;
c) removing the first solvent; and
d) combining the supramolecular polymer gel and the second solvent with magnetizable particles,
wherein the polymer gel comprises crosslinks formed by hydrophobic/hydrophilic interactions, Van der Waals interactions, π-π stacking bonds, donor-acceptor interactions, metal coordination bonds and combinations thereof.
